          <head>Collection of texts for the Ninth of Av </head>
          <msContents rend="visible">
            <summary>Collection of texts for the Ninth of Av in Hebrew and Judeo-Arabic</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="he"/>
            <msItem rend="visible">
              <locus from="1r" to="59v"/>
              <textLang mainLang="he"/>
              <author/>
              <title xml:lang="he">קינות לתשעה באב</title>
              <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳinot le-Tishʻah be-Av</title>
              <incipit/>
              <note><p>Including lamentation liturgies for Ninth of Av (1a-9), the kerovah for the
                  Ninth of Av, וארץ שפל רומי ונקלה כבודי by <persName>Shelomoh ben
                    Yehudah</persName>, and daytime lamentations for the Ninth of
                  Av.</p><p>Incomplete at the beginning (Hebrew foliation shows that at least 6
                  leaves are missing).</p></note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem rend="visible">
              <locus from="60r" to="61r"/>
              <textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr"/>
              <title xml:lang="he">מספורי החורבן בערבית</title>
              <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Me-sipure ha-Ḥurban be-ʿaravit</title>
              <note><p>Stories of the destruction of the Temple in
                  Judeo-Arabic.</p><p>Incomplete.</p></note>
            </msItem>
            <msItem rend="visible">
              <locus from="62r" to="74v"/>
              <textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr"/>
              <title xml:lang="he">הפטרה לט"ב בתרגום ערבי</title>
              <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hafṭarah la-Ṭ[isha] b[e-Av] be-targum ʿaravi</title>
              <note><p>Jeremiah 8:13-9:24 in Arabic translation.</p><p>Incomplete at the
                end.</p></note>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc rend="visible">
            <p>Paper codex of the 18th century.</p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="chart">
                <support>Paper withg laid lines and chain lines, <watermark>watermark is partially
                    visible: "ALLA ... COL...".</watermark></support>
                <extent>74 folios (i+74+i)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                    <height>117</height>
                    <width>90</width>
                  </dimensions><dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                    <height>90</height>
                    <width>62</width>
                  </dimensions></extent>
                <foliation><p>Foliation in Arabic numerals in pencil not counting the blank leaves
                    between fols. 59 and 60 and fols. 60 and 61. Parallel Hebrew foliation in ink
                    (fol. 1=fol. ז), which includes the blank leaves.</p></foliation>
                <collation><p>13 quires: i<hi rend="sup">4</hi>, ii<hi rend="sup">8</hi>, iii<hi
                      rend="sup">8-3</hi>, iv-xi<hi rend="sup">8</hi>, xii<hi rend="sup">6</hi>,
                      xiii<hi rend="sup">4</hi>. Quire ix, x, and xi also includes unfoliated blank
                    leaves.</p><p> Lacunae after fols. 4, 64, 70.</p><p>There is no lacuna between
                    fol. 17 and 18, thus the 3 leaves which were cut off at the end of quire iii,
                    must have been removed during production.</p></collation>
                <condition><p>Usage stains, smudged ink.</p><p>Water damage.</p></condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="1"><p>Not uniform layout.</p><p>Initial words at the beginning of
                    sections are in bigger, square script, often decorated.</p><p>Ruling is
                    visible.</p></layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="1">
              <summary>Sephardi semi-cursive and square scripts.</summary>
              <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote type="initial">Decorated initial words (e.g. 56v).</decoNote>
              <decoNote>Pen drawing of a human figure and a plant? on fol. 61bv.</decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions/>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding>
                <p>Post-1600, green cloth binding. </p>
                <p>Spine with M. Gaster's label: 'קינות Maroco &amp; HebrArab Haftara XVII.'</p>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
